Othaya girls school Principal has been crowned winner of 2020 African Union Continental Teacher of the Year award. Jane Kimiti scooped the AU continental award for best teacher in Adis Ababa on December 21. Kamiti was awarded for engaging in quality teaching which results in high standards of student achievement. She was also recognised for encouraging desirable behaviour among students through positive feedback and other methods. Engaging in activities and networks that enhance the social and cultural value of learnning and helping students to achieve their long term career goals by organising engagement with relevant agencies and information. Last year she was awarded for her outstanding innovation in the school that has enabled integration of Information Communication Technology (ICT) in teaching and learning. The Othaya Girlsâ€™ Principal has also introduced an e-learning section in the school.